RACE.FOOTNOTES: SKY ROCKER broke inward to brush GOLD MEMORIES at the start, settled into a duel on the lead from three wide in the first turn, continued to press the pace to the far turn, took command when called upon shaking off the speed rivals, opened a clear advantage in upper stretch and was not seriously challenged to the wire in a well managed ride. BLOOD ORANGE taken in hand to be near the back of the field early, steadily picked up rivals down the backside, circled five wide at the quarter pole and finished well to be a clear second best. GOLD MEMORIES crowded leaving the gate bumping rivals, was reserved off the pace to the far turn, waited to commence his rally turning for home, angled out following the runner-up and made steady gains down the lane. LA VALEDORA sped to the lead from between horses in the first turn, continued to duel for three-quarters of a mile and weakened in the stretch. THEHUNKSCLASSYLADY taken well in hand to be mid-pack early on, dropped back down the backside losing position and made a mild rally coming home. JULIE'S PASSION slow early to be at the back for the first half mile and made late gains passing tiring rivals. SHACK IT TO ME well placed from between horses to track the leaders in striking position through the second turn and failed to respond when called upon for the drive. NOMOROTHAT raced four wide in the first turn, moved up into contention down the backside and came up empty after five-eighths of a mile. ALONG CAME THUNDER raced headstrong into the first turn trying to get out from between rivals, dropped back entering the far turn and was never a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPERCENTS started a step slow to trail early, reserved well off pace to the turn, made up ground through the turn, split horses coming for home and closed with a rush to be up in time.
